%N A226188 Least positive integer k such that 1 + 1/2 + ... + 1/k > 2n/3.
%C A226188 Conjecture: a(n+1)/a(n) converges to 1.94...
%C A226188 Conjecture confirmed: series expansion of HarmonicNumber(k) gives a(n+1)/a(n) -> exp(2/3) = 1.947734... - _Jean-François Alcover_, Jun 05 2013
%C A226188 For n = 28..67 the values were certified by checking H_{a(n)-1} <= 2n/3 < H_{a(n)} using outward-rounded MPFR/GMP interval arithmetic. - _Carlo Corti_, Jun 27 2026
%H A226188 Carlo Corti, <a href="/A226188/b226188.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..67</a>
%H A226188 Carlo Corti, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20960659">Computational Extension of OEIS Sequence A226188: Certified Inverse Harmonic Thresholds up to n=67</a>, Zenodo archive, 2026.
%F A226188 a(n) = A226187(2*n); a(3*m) = A002387(2*m) for m >= 1. - _Carlo Corti_, Jun 27 2026
%e A226188 a(8) = 116 because 1 + 1/2 + ... + 1/115 < 16/3 < 1 + 1/2 + ... + 1/116.
%t A226188 z = 18; f[n_] := 1/n; Do[s = 0; a[n] = NestWhile[# + 1 &, 1, ! (s += f[#]) >= 2n/3 &], {n, 1, z}]; m = Map[a, Range[z]]
%o A226188 (Python)
%o A226188 from fractions import Fraction
%o A226188 from sympy import harmonic
%o A226188 from oeis_sequences.OEISsequences import bsearch
%o A226188 def A226188(n): return bsearch(harmonic,Fraction(2*n,3))+1 # _Chai Wah Wu_, Jun 27 2026
